<Content>Good budget hotel I stayed at The Belfort Hotel from 9th Feb 2007 for 3 nights. This hotel is ideal if your looking for somewhere to put your head down and use a base. There is a tram stop right outside which makes it convinient for getting in and out of town- even though they stop at midnight .There is a night bus but I found it easier to get a taxi- approx 20-25 Euros.It takes approx 10-15 minutes to get into the centre on the tram- they run about every 5-10 minutes.If you are expecting a three star hotel -beware - it is more like a high standard hostel. I went with 3 other friends and we are all in our early twentys, so it didn't bother us that it could get quite noisey. Most of the other guests were quite young.Breakfast was good-mostly consisting of cold meats, cheese and bread rolls... but it was nice.Staff were friendly and room was kept clean and towells changed daily.There were safes in the reception area which are free to use.All in all- don't expect luxury but this hotel does tend to come up cheper than most others and if you're on a budget its perfect. 
